just_use channels.go

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Load-bearing predicate: CanAccess(userID, channelID). Public channels are
visible to everyone; private (invite_only) channels require a subscriptions
row. Flags, messages, reactions, and events-filtering all call through here
rather than re-implementing the join — keep this the one place that knows
what "access" means.

Channel descriptions live in a separate channel_descriptions table (UPSERT
via ON CONFLICT) so channels rows stay small and editable independently.
